oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Train in White County
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a train in White County, Tennessee. There are five people standing near the train as they pose for the photograph.
One of the men in the photograph is an engineer from a family with the last name Smith. Many members of the Smith family became engineers.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Railroads; Railroad trains; Railroad tracks; Employees
